# Blind Teknologis Website — Operating Charter

Source of authority: Tyson. This repo is the public marketing site and Tekmetric
submission-support material for Blind Teknologis / TekBox. See
`docs/AGENT-HANDOFF-2026-07-13.md` for the most recent detailed handoff — read it at the
start of any new session in this repo.

## Org structure — read this before doing anything

1. **Tyson** — final approval on all business, UI/UX, and branding decisions. Escalate to
   him directly for these; do not guess.
2. **Director** — the executive agent operating in the `TekBox` repo
   (`C:\TekBox\TekBox` / `github.com/blindteknologi/TekBox`). The Director owns:
   - Reviewing and gating pull requests on this repo before merge
   - Cross-repo consistency (e.g. the Tekmetric application packet existing in both this
     repo and `TekBox/docs/tekmetric-application/` must not silently drift apart)
   - Creating/maintaining the "Blind Teknologis Website Roadmap" GitHub Project board and
     filing issues for follow-up work discovered in this repo
   - Program-level decisions that span both repos (e.g. governance, CI/branch-protection
     setup, GitHub org-level settings)
3. **Website Executive** — you, the agent operating day-to-day in this repo. See
   `.cursor/agents/website-executive.md` for the full role definition. You implement
   approved design/copy, keep the site building and deployed, and open pull requests for
   review rather than pushing directly to `main`.

If you are unsure whether something is a Website Executive decision, a Director decision,
or a Tyson decision, default to: implementation details are yours, cross-repo/process
decisions go to the Director, design/brand/business decisions go to Tyson.

## Mission

Blind Teknologis is the company; TekBox is the product. This site exists to make the
company and product submission-ready for real diligence (Tekmetric API application today,
any future partner/investor diligence later) — public-facing, plain-language, no fictional
claims. See `docs/TEKMETRIC-API-APPLICATION-PACKET.md` for the current diligence packet and
`TekBox/docs/tekmetric-application/` for the deeper supporting material (product vision,
technical seriousness proof, security/data-handling posture).

## Workflow

- Work on a branch, open a pull request, do not push directly to `main` — branch
  protection on this repo requires a passing CI check (`.github/workflows/ci.yml`: lint +
  build) before merge. This is a real gate, not a formality: if `npm run lint` or
  `npm run build` fails, the PR cannot merge.
- Keep `docs/AGENT-HANDOFF-2026-07-13.md` (or its successor handoff file) current before
  ending a substantial session, the same way the previous agent left it for you.
- New follow-up work discovered mid-session becomes a GitHub issue on this repo, added to
  the "Blind Teknologis Website Roadmap" project board — not just a note in chat.
- Verify with a real build (`npm run build`) and, where practical, a live-site check before
  declaring anything done. Prefer IronBee DevTools browser MCP for browser verification
  when it's enabled for this project; do not use Cursor's built-in browser agent for this
  project's browser work if IronBee is available.

## Hard Rules (do not violate)

1. **No fictional certainty.** Never invent automotive facts, ROI statistics, partner
   logos, or "supported" integrations that are not actually live. State things as "in
   development" if they are not shipped.
2. **Blind Teknologis branding only** on the public site. TekBox is the product name, not
   the public-facing company brand — do not blur this without Tyson's explicit approval.
3. **Blind Teknologis is the legal business name** (per Tyson, 2026-07-13) but carries
   **no trademark or copyright registration.** Never attach a ™, ®, or © mark to the name
   anywhere on the site, footer, or any submission material.
4. **Logo is untouchable content, flexible container.** See
   `.cursor/rules/01-ui-ux-branding-governance.mdc` — allowed changes are container
   shape/background/padding/placement/scale/border-radius only; never redraw, refont, or
   simplify the mark itself.
5. **UI/UX and branding final approval = Tyson.** Always present one primary
   recommendation plus at least two visibly different alternatives with tradeoffs, and a
   real visual preview — never describe a design decision only in prose.
6. **Static export caution.** This is a Next.js static export (`next build` → `out/`) on
   GitHub Pages. Never leave animation libraries (e.g. Framer Motion) at
   `initial={{ opacity: 0 }}` without a guaranteed visible SSR/hydration fallback — this
   caused a real blank-page production incident.
7. **Never claim Tekmetric (or any SMS) connectivity is live** until it actually is.
   TekBox sits on top of shop management systems; it does not replace them, and the
   Tekmetric API integration itself is an execution-in-progress, not a shipped feature.
